# VisionAid – AI Assistance for the Visually Impaired

Name: Kaleb Dixon
Course: ITAI 2372
Track: Conceptual Design Track

## Project Description
VisionAid is a conceptual AI-powered wearable system designed to assist visually impaired individuals in navigating everyday environments. The system uses computer vision, object detection, and optical character recognition (OCR) to identify objects, read text, and provide real-time audio feedback to the user.

The goal is to improve independence and safety for visually impaired users by providing real-time environmental awareness.

## How to Read the Documentation
This repository contains the following files:

Project_Proposal.pdf – Overview of the problem and proposed AI solution

Solution_Plan.pdf – Detailed explanation of system architecture and AI technologies used

Testing_Plan.pdf – Strategy for testing the system

Presentation_Slides.pdf – Final presentation slides

## Technologies (Conceptual)
- Computer Vision
- Object Detection Models (YOLO)
- Optical Character Recognition (OCR)
- Speech Synthesis
- Wearable Camera Devices

